<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1110 Wallace, Henry A./83:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-15T20:00:00-04:00">March 15, 1943—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>311. Your 348, March 12, 9 p.m. The Vice President states flatly that if
                            any such arrangements are being made they are without his knowledge or
                            consent since he does not intend to see Haya de la Torre.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>